==English==
===Etymology===
Proprietary name, from French [[oui]] + German [[ja]], both ‘yes’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈwi:ʤə/}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Ouija'''
# a [[board]], having [[letter]]s of the [[alphabet]] and the words [[yes]] and [[no]]; used with a [[planchette]] during a [[seance]] to "[[communicate]]" with [[spirit]]s

